{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"How rounding is done"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/bigint\/aboutdivision"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/AboutDivision"},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"BigInt"}],"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","title":"About Division"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"kind":"article","seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Articles","identifiers":["doc:\/\/BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/AboutBInt","doc:\/\/BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/AboutBFraction","doc:\/\/BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/AboutCRT","doc:\/\/BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/Algorithms","doc:\/\/BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/Performance","doc:\/\/BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/References"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Articles"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"","level":2,"text":""},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If an integer "},{"code":"x","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" divided by "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"d"},{"type":"text","text":" gives quotient "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"q"},{"type":"text","text":" and remainder "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"r"},{"type":"text","text":", then it is true that"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"x = d * q + r"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"|r| < |d|"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For given x and d, if the remainder is not zero, there will be two possible (q, r) pairs. For example:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"11 \/ 4 = (2, 3) and 11 \/ 4 = (3, -1)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"and"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"-11 \/ 4 = (-2, -3) and -11 \/ 4 = (-3, 1)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"quotientAndRemainder(dividingBy:)"},{"type":"text","text":" methods return the quotient rounded towards zero and the corresponding remainder."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"quotientAndRemainderCeil(dividingBy:)"},{"type":"text","text":" methods return the quotient rounded towards "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"+Infinity"},{"type":"text","text":" and the corresponding remainder."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"quotientAndRemainderFloor(dividingBy:)"},{"type":"text","text":" methods return the quotient rounded towards "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"-Infinity"},{"type":"text","text":" and the corresponding remainder."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the remainder is in fact zero, the methods return the same quotient."}]}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt"]]},"references":{"doc://BigInt/documentation/BigInt/AboutCRT":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/AboutCRT","role":"article","url":"\/documentation\/bigint\/aboutcrt","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Chinese Remainder Theorem"}],"kind":"article","title":"About CRT"},"doc://BigInt/documentation/BigInt/Algorithms":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/Algorithms","role":"article","url":"\/documentation\/bigint\/algorithms","kind":"article","title":"Algorithms","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Some of the algorithms used in BigInt are described below"}]},"doc://BigInt/documentation/BigInt":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/bigint","title":"BigInt","abstract":[{"text":"Signed integers and fractions of unbounded size","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://BigInt/documentation/BigInt/Performance":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/Performance","url":"\/documentation\/bigint\/performance","title":"Performance","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Execution times for certain BigInt operations"}],"role":"article","kind":"article","type":"topic"},"doc://BigInt/documentation/BigInt/AboutBInt":{"kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/bigint\/aboutbint","identifier":"doc:\/\/BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/AboutBInt","title":"About BInt","role":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Signed integers of unbounded size"}],"type":"topic"},"doc://BigInt/documentation/BigInt/References":{"kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Algorithms from the following books and papers have been used in the implementation","type":"text"}],"role":"article","url":"\/documentation\/bigint\/references","identifier":"doc:\/\/BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/References","title":"References","type":"topic"},"doc://BigInt/documentation/BigInt/AboutBFraction":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/AboutBFraction","url":"\/documentation\/bigint\/aboutbfraction","role":"article","kind":"article","type":"topic","title":"About BFraction","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Signed fractions with numerator and denominator of unbounded size"}]}}}